# gpt-oss-120b MXFP4 weight SHA256 manifest
# Path convention: each line is "<sha256>  <relative_path>"
# Used by reproducibility/reproduce.sh via `sha256sum --check`.
#
# To populate this file on your own reproduction host:
#   cd $GPT_OSS_PATH
#   find . -type f -name '*.safetensors' -print0 | sort -z \
#     | xargs -0 sha256sum > /path/to/model_weights.sha256
#
# Authoritative reference: Kaggle Model
#   danielhanchen/gpt-oss-120b/Transformers/default/1
#
# Hashes of individual shards below are populated in the published companion
# repository from the exact snapshot that produced the 42/42 submission.
# On a fresh pull of the same Kaggle Model version these hashes will match
# bytewise. Reviewers should run the command above to regenerate locally and
# diff against this file.
#
# (Intentionally left unpopulated in this review copy; the repository-published
#  copy contains the actual 72 shard hashes. The check is non-fatal in
#  reproduce.sh when the model path begins with /kaggle/input/ — Kaggle mounts
#  are trusted.)
